<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She recently joined the cobbles as escort Nicky Wheatley. </p>

<p>And Coronation Street newcomer Kimberly Hart-Simpson cut a casual figure as she enjoyed a pampering session in Manchester on Tuesday.</p>

<p>The actress showcased her toned figure in a grey plunging jumpsuit with a yellow vest top underneath as she was seen entering The CryoLab, which offers a cryotherapy chamber, Brazilian bum lifts and cellulite treatments. </p>

<p>Stepping out: Coronation Street newcomer Kimberly Hart-Simpson cut a casual figure as she enjoyed a pampering session in Manchester on Tuesday</p>

<p>Adding other low-key details, Kimberly opted for a black New York Yankees baseball cap and silver trainers.</p>

<p>The actress added a touch of luxury in the form of a Burberry handbag and silver jewellery.</p>

<p>Kimberly will no doubt be enjoying an afternoon of pampering after joining the cobbles as escort Nicky Wheatley.</p>

<p>The character has developed an unusual relationship with Daniel Osbourne after he lost his wife, Sinead, to cancer last year. </p>

<p>Pampering session: The actress showcased her toned figure in a grey plunging jumpsuit with a yellow vest top underneath as she was seen entering The CryoLab, which offers a cryotherapy chamber, Brazilian bum lifts and cellulite treatments</p>

<p>Low-key: Adding other low-key details, Kimberly opted for a black New York Yankees baseball cap and silver trainers</p>

<p>Yet things have recently taken a sinister turn as Daniel has been asking Nicky to wear Sinead's clothes and perfume.  </p>

<p>Only recently, Kimberly revealed she has been trying to get a role on Coronation Street for ten years.</p>

<p>She told Inside Soap: 'My first ever audition for Coronation Street was probably about 10 years ago, when I'd just finished drama school. I completely over-acted!</p>

<p>A touch of luxury! The actress added a touch of luxury in the form of a Burberry handbag and silver jewellery</p>

<p>'I was so hammy because I couldn't understand the difference between doing theatre and TV.'</p>

<p>She added: 'But with the role of Nicky, I only auditioned once – I just walked into the room and thought, "I'm having this one!"'</p>

<p>Kimberly sweetly added that it was her late father's dream for her to secure a role on the cobbles.</p>

<p>She told The Sun: 'Unfortunately, I lost my dad in 2007. One of the last things he said to me was, "Just do me a favour and get on Corrie, love." We had that shared ­connection with it.'</p>

